[[!meta title="Virt-manager"]]

Running Tails from an ISO image
===============================

1. Start virt-manager
2. Connect to QEMU: XXX
   - If you already had a connection to QEMU configured
     - Click on "localhost (QEMU)"
3. File → New Virtual Machine
   1. Step 1
      - Local install media (ISO image or CDROM)
      - Forward
   2. Step 2
      - Use ISO image → Browse... → Browse Local
      - Choose an operating system type and version
        - OS type: Generic
        - Version: Generic
   3. Step 3
      - Memory (RAM): 1024 MB
      - Forward
   4. Step 4
      - Enable storage for this virtual machine: No
      - Forward
   5. Step 5
      - Name
      - Advanced options: to change network type
      - Finish
   The Virual Machine start automatically
If you get "Error starting domain: Requested operation is not valid:
network 'default' is not active"
  - localhost (QEMU)
  - Connection Details
  - Virtual Networks
  - default
  - "play" icon (Start Network)

Running Tails from a USB stick or SD card
=========================================

1. "View" → "Details"
2. "Add Hardware" → "USB Host Device"
3. Select USB → Finish
4. Boot Options

Running Tails from a virtual USB device
=======================================

1. "View" → "Details"
2. "Add Hardware" → "Storage"
   - "Bus type": USB
3. Click "USB Disk 1" in left pane
   Check "Removable"
